-07T10:25:46Z", "closed_at": "2016-07-07T10:25:46Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "To ensure that `sizeof(&mut T::A) == sizeof(&Cell<T::A>)` I bound T::A with Sized. But the followng still fails to compile:\n\n``` rust\nuse std::mem;\nuse std::cell::Cell;\n\nstruct XX;\n\ntrait Trait { type A: Sized; }\nimpl Trait for XX { type A = u8; }\n\n// this works\nfn mutref_to_cell_1<T: Sized>(v: &mut T) -> &Cell<T> {\n    unsafe { mem::transmute(v) }\n}\n\n// this doesn't (apparently it doesn't see that T::A is Sized)\nfn mutref_to_cell_2<T: Trait>(v: &mut T::A) -> &Cell<T::A> {\n    unsafe { mem::transmute(v) }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let mut y: u8 = 100; \n    println!(\"{:?}\", mutref_to_cell_1::<u8>(&mut y));\n    println!(\"{:?}\", mutref_to_cell_2::<XX>(&mut y));\n}\n```\n\nError:\n\n```\n<anon>:16:14: 16:28 error: transmute called on types with potentially different sizes:\n    &mut <T as Trait>::A (could be 64 bits) to\n    &core::cell::Cell<<T as Trait>::A> (could be 128 bits)\n```\n", "closed_by": {"login": "abandoned-cocoon", "id": 15789, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1Nzg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/15789?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon", "html_url": "https://github.com/abandoned-cocoon", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/abandoned-cocoon/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.co